011/**
012 * A palette of predefined colors as packed IPT floats, the kind {@link ColorTools} works with.
013 * You can access colors by their constant name, such as {@code OCEAN_BLUE}, by the {@link #NAMED} map using
014 * {@code NAMED.get("Ocean Blue", 0f)}, or by index in the FloatArray called {@link #LIST}. Note that to access a float
015 * color from NAMED, you need to give a default value if the name is not found; {@code 0f} is a good default because it
016 * will not occur in a valid IPT color. You can access the names in a specific order with {@link #NAMES} (which is
017 * alphabetical), {@link #NAMES_BY_HUE} (which is sorted by the hue of the matching color, from red to yellow to blue
018 * (with gray around here) to purple to red again), or {@link #NAMES_BY_LIGHTNESS} (which is sorted by the intensity of
019 * the matching color, from darkest to lightest). Having a name lets you look up the matching color in {@link #NAMED}.
020 * <br>
021 * Created by Tommy Ettinger on 10/13/2020.
022 */
023public class Palette {
024    public static final ObjectFloatOrderedMap<String> NAMED = new ObjectFloatOrderedMap<>(256);
025    public static final FloatList LIST = new FloatList(256);
